(23, '19 DAYS EXPERIENCE NATURE & BEAUTY OF SUMATRA PLUS CUBADAK ISLAND LEISURE', '<div align=\"justify\">Discover Sumatra Elephant,Sumatra Orang Utan and other kind of flora and fauna of National park<br>Explore the Jungle of Sumatra and get amazing experience during your holiday in Leuser National park.<br>Enjoy the rewarding naturalist\'s experience and exploring the pristine Leuser Ecosystem<br>Discover the incredible and diverse beauty highlights in North and West Sumatera by land journeys.<br>Discover the impressive and pristine rainforest of Sumatra, its history, and culture<br>The Secret of North and West Sumatra combined in your tour.<br>Relaxing on the beach of Cubadak Island,slowing down and soaking up the sunshine, stay in a beautiful rustic resort owned by a welcoming French couple, making it a heavenly island hideaway with delicious food to boot. Spend your days hiking to Cubadakâ€™s interior, snorkelling coral reefs and collapsing on the sand. <br></div>					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                ', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m76!1m12!1m3!1d4084522.002001356!2d96.99799124119214!3d1.3002283089123594!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m61!3e0!4m5!1s0x303131cc1c3eb2fd%3A0x23d431c8a6908262!2sMedan%2C%20Medan%20City%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.5951956!2d98.67222269999999!4m5!1s0x3030b4c7e67e2c7d%3A0x209df7765468fec3!2sTangkahan!3m2!1d3.6962631!2d98.0691646!4m5!1s0x3030c81b5f04b997%3A0xd57e31753995db8f!2sBukit%20Lawang!3m2!1d3.5552618!2d98.1447804!4m5!1s0x3031028adff333f9%3A0x5eba62355c88647b!2sBerastagi!3m2!1d3.185291!2d98.504913!4m5!1s0x3031e8022c23c201%3A0x9e185a1f1c3da745!2sSamosir%2C%20Samosir%20Regency%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d2.6273112!2d98.7922018!4m5!1s0x302c268bdbcf3a1d%3A0xef63c1f0315bdcd!2sSipirok!3m2!1d1.612708!2d99.26151999999999!4m5!1s0x2fd538a460df4be1%3A0xc940d13d891ab206!2sBukittinggi!3m2!1d-0.30391779999999996!2d100.383479!4m5!1s0x2fd56a8c17698059%3A0x83416c96b66fd2cd!2sPuncak%20Lawang!3m2!1d-0.26421839999999996!2d100.2426273!4m5!1s0x2fd4b942e2b117bb%3A0xb8468cb5c3046ba5!2sPadang%2C%20Padang%20City%2C%20West%20Sumatra!3m2!1d-0.9470831999999999!2d100.417181!4m5!1s0x2fd358596237c14d%3A0x5d0658b2314c20b7!2sCubadak%20Paradiso%20Village%2C%20South%20Pesisir%20Regency%2C%20West%20Sumatra!3m2!1d-1.217416!2d100.40019!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sid!4v1576950421709!5m2!1sen!2sid\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>', '<p align=\"justify\"><b>                                                    DAY 01: AIRPORT â€“ HOTEL / CITY TOURÂ  (Emerald Garden Hotel /Le Polonia Hotel / similar) <br></b>Arrival at Kualanamu International Airport Medan meet and transfer to hotel and then city tour by visiting Great Mosque, Sultan Palace, Chinese Temple and market , afternoon return back to hotel.<br>Â Â  Â <br><b>DAY 02: MEDAN â€“ TANGKAHAN (Mega Inn Lodge)Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Tangkahan via Binjai and Tanjung Pura, on the way visit several villages where you can see the daily activities of local people, arrival at Tangkahan (a part of Leuser National Park) check in to simple Guesthouse. Afternoon free at own leisure or walking around the area of the hotel. On the bank of the river and the will be possibility to see the elephants washing on the river.<br><br><b>DAY 03: TANGKAHAN â€“ ELEPHANT WASHING & RIVER SAFARIÂ Â Â Â Â Â Â  (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the elephant station and then joinÂ  with the Mahout during washing the elephant, and then feed the elephant. After feeding the elephant enjoying Tubing through the river and stop will be made at fantastic Buluh Waterfall where you may enjoy the waterfall, take your natural shower and then you can enjoy sun-bathing and swimming on the river and enjoying picnic lunch on the bank of the river. Afternoon arrival at the village you can get in touch with local people, where you can see the daily activities of the local people and then return to guesthouse by walking, arrival at guesthouse you can take a rest or visit hot springs and waterfall near the guesthouse. <br><br><b>DAY 04: TANGKAHAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG (Bukit Lawang Cottages / Rindu Alam Hotel / similar)Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Bukit Lawang by Jeep , on the way stop at several plantations for rubber, and palm oil, arrival at Bukit Lawang check-in to hotel and afternoon free at own leisure.<br>Â Â  Â Â Â Â  Â Â Â  Â <br><b>DAY 05: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ TRACKINGÂ Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore the nature of Leuser National Park with its flora and fauna, there will be possibility to see Orang Utan on their own habitat and other kind of animals such as Thomas-leaf monkeys, long tail maccaque, gibbon, black gibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain-forest. This tracking will take about 03 hours, after tracking return to hotel.<br>Afternoon free at own leisure to enjoy the nature of Bukit Lawang where you can also walking to the village around the hotel <br><br><b>DAY 06: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ BRASTAGI (Hotel Sinabung Hills / Sibayak Intl Hotel / Grand Mutiara Hotel)Â Â Â Â Â  (B) <br></b>After breakfast drive to Brastagi , on the way stop at Sembahe River, passing Sibolangit, and arrival at Brastagi visiting Lhumbini Park with its duplicate of Shwedagon pagoda, then visit fruit market, and Gundaling Hill. Afternoon check-in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 07: BRASTAGI â€“ SAMOSIR / LAKE TOBA ( Tabo Cottages / Samosir Villa)Â Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Parapat , on the way visit Batak Karo traditional village at Dokan, stop at Sipiso-piso waterfall, visit at Rumah Bolon (Long House) the old palace of Batak Simalungun Kings and Simarjarunjung to see the view of Lake Toba, upon arrival at Parapat crossing to Samosir Island by ferry boat , arriving on Samosir check-in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 08: MOTOR BIKE TOURÂ Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast you may choose to explore Samosir Island â€œthe Land of Batak Toba peopleâ€ by Motorcycle to the Top of Samosir Hill to see small Lake at the Top of the Hill called Sidahoni Lake, where on the way visiting several Batak Toba villages, to see the activities of local people such us visiting children on the school, visiting the village where the local people make traditional hand weaving and other activities. When you prefer tracking, our tour guide will accompany tracking to the jungle on Samosir Island with the possibility to stop at several villages. Afternoon return to hotel. <br><br><b>DAY 09: SAMOSIR FREE AT OWN LEISUREÂ Â  (B)<br></b>Today is a free time to relax, swimming, sun-bathing or walking around the villages and still possible to take a Boat tripÂ  (Optional Tour)<br><br><b>DAY 10: SAMOSIR â€“ SIPIROK (Tor Sibohi Hotel)Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast crossing back to Parapat by ferry boat and arrival at Parapat drive to Sipirok, on the way stop at pineapple, clove, and coffee plantation and visiting traditional market at Balige Sigur-gur and Sipoholon Hotsprings. Before arrival at Sipirok the day enjoy the nature by walking at the bank of Sarulla river, the ricefieldsÂ  terraces and arrival at Sipirok check-in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 11: SIPIROK â€“ BUKITTINGGI (Royal Denai Hotel / Similar)Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>Leave Sipirok for Bukittinggi by passing rain tropical forest of Rimba Panti and stop will be made to see the attraction of monkey picking up the coconut. Visit pepper, vanilla, cardamom and cinnamon garden, and crossing the equator line at Bonjol, afternoon arrival at Bukittinggi - the charming town of Minangkabau people - directly check-in to hotel. <br><br><b>Day 12: BUKITTINGGI â€“ CITY TOUR â€“ HARAU VALLEYÂ Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Payakumbuh and visiting Harau Valley with its Echo, ricefield in terraces, traditional villages and then back to Bukittinggi , visiting Sianok Canyon, Fort De Kock, Museum and Market. Afternoon return back to hotel. Evening enjoy traditional Minangkabau Dance and traditional music performance.<br><br><b>DAY 13: BUKITTINGGI MINANGKABAU TOURÂ Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Batusangkar via Tabek Patah, on the way stop at Rao-Rao to visit Minangkabau traditional village and stop to see traditional coffee milling, arrival at Batusangkar proceed to Pagaruyung to visit the duplicate Palace of Minangkabau Kingdom, afternoon return to Bukittinggi via Padang Panjang and visit Pandai Sikat village to see Minangkabau traditional hand weaving and wood carving.<br>Â  Â <br><b>DAY 14: BUKITTINGGI â€“ EXPLORE LOCAL PEOPLE ACTIVITIESÂ  (B)<br></b>After breakfast visit several villages to see how the local people on their daily activities, such as planting the rice on rice-field, and farmer working on their field which helped by water buffalo, and even experience the local people during harvesting time. On this day will provide traditional fried tapioca or fried banana as your snack cooked at the house of local people.<br>Â Â Â  Â <br><b>DAY 15: BUKITTINGGI â€“ PUNCAK LAWANG TRACKING â€“ BUKITTINGGIÂ Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Puncak Lawang, on the way stop at Koto Gadang village to see traditional silverwork and arrival at Puncak Lawang tracking to Maninjau via Lawang jungle , on the way down to Lake Maninjau enjoying coffee break at traditional coffee shop in the jungle, during the tracking there is opportunity to walk at the bank of ricefield and villages. Upon arrival at Maninjau, enjoying the nature of the lake, afternoon return to Bukittinggi.<br><br><b>Day 16: BUKITTINGGI â€“ PADANG â€“ CUBADAK ISLAND (Cubadak Paradiso Resort)Â Â Â Â Â  (B,D)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Padang via Padang Panjang, on the way stop at Anai waterfall, arrival in Padang transfer to Painan takes another 2 hours and boat crossing to Cubadak Island (30 minutes) , arriving at Cubadak Island check-in to hotel<br><br><b>Day 17: CUBADAK PARADISO ISLANDÂ Â  (B,L,D)<br></b>Today is the activities on the island which will be arranged by the resort, the activities can be covered :<br>-Â Â  Â Snorkelling with its Snorkeling equipment<br>-Â Â  Â Picnic days to neighbouring island (Depend on the weather)<br>-Â Â  Â Canoeing and Fun Sailing<br>-Â Â  Â Tracking in the forest.<br>Fullboard meals (Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner) during stay in the Island included + Free flow of Sumatra tea and Coffee<br><br><b>Day 18: CUBADAK PARADISO ISLANDÂ Â Â Â  (B,L,D)<br></b>Today is the activities on the island which will be arranged by the resort, the activities can be covered :<br>-Â Â  Â Snorkelling with its Snorkeling equipment<br>-Â Â  Â Picnic days to neighbouring island (Depend on the weather)<br>-Â Â  Â Canoeing and Fun Sailing<br>-Â Â  Â Tracking in the forest<br>Fullboard meals (Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner) during stay in the Island included + Free flow of Sumatra tea and Coffee.<br><br><b>Day 19: CUBADAK ISLAND â€“ PADANG / AIRPORTÂ Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast crossing back to Painan by boat and then drive to Padang Airport for your flight to next destination.<br>Tour End<br><br><b>Included : <br></b>- Accommodation based on Twin sharing <br>- Air-Condition private car <br>- Daily Breakfast <br>- Tours <br>- Transfers <br>- Entrance fee <br>- Elephant wshing at Tangkahan + elephant feeding <br>- Tubing at Tangkahan + picnic lunch <br>- local non-ac jeep for transfer from Tangkahan to Bukit Lawang <br>- Jungle tracking at Bukit Lawang (03 hours) included local guide & permit <br>- Excursion at Samosir Island by car Â <br>- Ferry boat crossing Parapat to Samosir and Painan to Cubadak Island vice-versa <br>- Puncak Lawang â€“ Maninjau tracking <br>- English speaking Tour guide (From day 01 until drop off at Padang for Cubadak Island) <br>- Fullboard meals during stay at Cubadak Island, excursion at Cubadak Island (Except diving).<br></p><p><b>Â Excluded :</b> Airfares and airport taxes, Lunch, Dinner, Insurance, Donation, Tips, Elephant riding at Tangkahan, Camera permit at Bukit Lawang and all personal gratuities.<br></p>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            '),
(24, '06 DAYS EXPLORE THE NATURE OF LEUSER NATIONAL PARK SUMATRA ELEPHANT & SUMATRA ORANG UTAN', '<div align=\"justify\">Discover Sumatra Elephant, Sumatra Orang Utan and other kind of flora and fauna of National park<br>Explore the Jungle of Sumatra and get amazing experience during your holiday in Leuser National park.<br>Enjoy the rewarding naturalist\'s experience and exploring the pristine Leuser Ecosystem</div>					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                ', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m46!1m12!1m3!1d509661.7415905114!2d98.19299246860326!3d3.648382387712278!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m31!3e0!4m5!1s0x30314a34dfa5662d%3A0xc536c90019a09ea6!2sKualanamu%20International%20Airport%2C%20Jalan%20Bandara%20Kuala%20Namu%2C%20Pasar%20Enam%20Kuala%20Namu%2C%20Deli%20Serdang%20Regency%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.6338253999999997!2d98.87730169999999!4m5!1s0x303131cc1c3eb2fd%3A0x23d431c8a6908262!2sMedan%2C%20Medan%20City%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.5951956!2d98.67222269999999!4m5!1s0x3030b4c7e67e2c7d%3A0x209df7765468fec3!2sTangkahan%2C%20Namu%20Sialang%2C%20Langkat%20Regency%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.6962631!2d98.0691646!4m5!1s0x3030c81b5f04b997%3A0xd57e31753995db8f!2sBukit%20Lawang%2C%20Langkat%20Regency%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.5552618!2d98.1447804!4m5!1s0x303131cc1c3eb2fd%3A0x23d431c8a6908262!2sMedan%2C%20Medan%20City%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.5951956!2d98.67222269999999!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sid!4v1576950582355!5m2!1sen!2sid\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>', '<div align=\"justify\"><b>DAY 01: ARRIVAL IN MEDAN (Le Polonia Hotel / Hotel Emerald Garden / similar) </b><br>Upon arrival at Kualanamu International Airport pick up by our tour guide and then Transfer to hotel, afternoon free at own leisure. <br><br><b>DAY 02: MEDAN â€“ CITY TOUR â€“ TANGKAHAN (Mega Inn Lodge)Â Â  (B) Â </b><br>After breakfast, pick up by our tour guide and then transfer to town for city tour visiting Sultan Palace, Great Mosque, Chinese Temple and then drive to Tangkahan via Binjai and Batang Serangan. Afternoon arrival at Tangkahan check-in at Mega Inn Lodge. <br><br><b>DAY 03: TANGKAHAN â€“ ELEPHANT WASHING & RIVER SAFARIÂ Â Â Â  (B,L)</b><br>After breakfast walking to the elephant station and then joinÂ  with the Mahout during washing the elephant, and then feed the elephant, after feeding the elephant enjoying Tubing through the river and stop will be made at fantastic Buluh Waterfall where you may enjoy the waterfall take your natural shower and enjoy sun bathing and swimming on the river and enjoying picnic lunch on the bank of the river. Afternoon arrival at the village you can get in touch with local people, where you can see the daily activities of the local people and then return to guesthouse by walking, arrival at guesthouse you can take a rest or visit hot springs and waterfall near the guesthouse. <br><br><b>DAY 04: TANGKAHAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG BY JEEP (Bukit Lawang Cottages / Rindu Alam Hotel / similar)Â Â  (B)</b><br>After breakfast leave Tangkahan for Bukit Lawang by Jeep passing plantations and jungle road, on the way stop at several interesting places (school) for enjoying the panorama and witness the activities of the local people. Upon arrival at Bukit Lawang check-in to hotel and afternoon free at own leisure to enjoy the nature of Bukit Lawang.<br><br><b>DAY 05: FULLDAY LEUSER NATIONAL PARK TRACKINGÂ  (B,L)</b><br>After breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore the nature of Leuser National Park with its flora and fauna, there will be possibility to see Orang Utan on their own habitat and other kind of animals such as Thomas-leaf monkeys, long tail maccaque, gibbon, black gibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain-forest. This full day tracking will finish in the afternoon. <br><br><b>DAY 06: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ MEDAN / AIRPORTÂ Â  (B)</b><br>After breakfast drive to Medan via Binjai, on the way visiting traditional market at Kuala, arrival in Medan directly transfer to Kualanamu International Airport for your flight to next destination.<br></div><br><div align=\"justify\"><b>Included:</b><br>-Accommodation in twin sharing<br>-Air condition private car<br>-Daily breakfast<br>-Tours<br>-Transfers<br>-Entrance fee<br>-English speaking tour guide<br>-Elephant washing + elephant feeding at Tangkahan<br>-Tubing at Tangkahan + picnic lunch<br>-Local non-aircon jeep for transfer from Tangkahan to Bukit Lawang<br>-Fullday jungle tracking at Bukit Lawang included: local guide, permit and picnic lunch<br><br><b>Excluded:</b><br>-Airfare, airport taxes, insurance, donation, tips, lunch, dinner, elephant riding at Tangkahan, camera permit at Bukit Lawang and all personal gratuities.<br></div><br>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        '),
(26, '07 DAYS MEDAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG ADVENTURE & SIBAYAK VULCANO CLIMBING', '<div align=\"justify\">Explore the nature of Leuser National Park , Watching Orang Utan â€œ One of the most intelligent primateâ€<br>A great time to learn more about these orange giants of the rainforest & Climbing Sibayak Vulcano and enjoying sunrise<br></div>					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                ', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m52!1m12!1m3!1d509745.63845283305!2d98.19299246703913!3d3.497341942800482!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m37!3e0!4m5!1s0x30314a34dfa5662d%3A0xc536c90019a09ea6!2sKualanamu%20International%20Airport%2C%20Jalan%20Bandara%20Kuala%20Namu%2C%20Pasar%20Enam%20Kuala%20Namu%2C%20Deli%20Serdang%20Regency%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.6338253999999997!2d98.87730169999999!4m5!1s0x303131cc1c3eb2fd%3A0x23d431c8a6908262!2sMedan%2C%20Medan%20City%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.5951956!2d98.67222269999999!4m5!1s0x3030b4c7e67e2c7d%3A0x209df7765468fec3!2sTangkahan%2C%20Namu%20Sialang%2C%20Langkat%20Regency%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.6962631!2d98.0691646!4m5!1s0x3030c81b5f04b997%3A0xd57e31753995db8f!2sBukit%20Lawang%2C%20Langkat%20Regency%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.5552618!2d98.1447804!4m5!1s0x3031028adff333f9%3A0x5eba62355c88647b!2sBerastagi%2C%20Gundaling%20II%2C%20Karo%20Regency%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.185291!2d98.504913!4m5!1s0x303131cc1c3eb2fd%3A0x23d431c8a6908262!2sMedan%2C%20Medan%20City%2C%20North%20Sumatra!3m2!1d3.5951956!2d98.67222269999999!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sid!4v1576950731323!5m2!1sen!2sid\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>', '<p align=\"justify\"><b>DAY 01: MEDANÂ  - BUKIT LAWANG (Bukit Lawang Cottage / Rindu Alam Hotel / similar)<br></b>Arrival at Kualanamu Internationasl Airport Medan meet service and then drive to Bukit Lawang with stop at several plantations for rubber and oilpalmÂ  , arrival at Bukit Lawang check-in to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 02: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ LEUSER PARK TRACKING (Overnight in TENT or SHELTER)Â Â Â  (B,L,D)<br></b>After breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore the nature of Leuser National park with its flora and fauna, there is possibility to see Orang Utan on their own habitat and other kind of animal such as Thomas -eaf monkeys, long tail maccaque, gibbon, black gibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain-forest.Â  Overnight in tent or shelter in the jungle. Lunch and dinner provided.<br><b><br>DAY 03: CONTINUE TRACKINGÂ  RETURN TO HOTEL (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast prepared by tour guide continue tracking, today is full day walking and explore the rain tropical forest with its wildlife living in their natural habitat. Afternoon return to hotelin Bukit Lawang.<br><b><br>DAY 04: FULLDAY WHITE WATER RAFTINGÂ Â  (B,L) <br></b>After breakfast drive by mini bus to Wampu River and arrival at starting point, start your white water rafting adventure. During the rafting, there is an excellent opportunity to see the birds and wild life as while enjoying the two mild rapids. Arrival at waterfall at the bank of the river enjoying your shower and lunch will be provided In afternoon arrival at the point stop enjoying coffee break before driving back to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 05: BUKIT LAWANG - BRASTAGIÂ  (Grand Mutiara Hotel / Sinabung Hills Hotel)Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Brastagi with stop at Sembahe river, arrival at Brastagi visiting fruit market, and Gundaling Hill. Afternoon check-in to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 06: SIBAYAK VOLCANO CLIMBING â€“ MEDAN (Emerald Garden Hotel /Le Polonia Hotel / similar)Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>At early morning transferred to the slope of Sibayak volcano and then hike up (~3 hrs to go and back) to the summit of Gunung Sibayak will reward you with sweeping views of the surrounding volcano landscape. The volcano is high in geothermal activity with fuming vents spewing out crystalline sulphur which was mined on a small scale in the past. There is a beautiful heart shaped crater lake where love wordings have been formed by visitors using the volcanic rocks.Â  Arrival at the peak of Sibayak volcano enjoying sun rise on the peak of Sibayak volcano and then time for making pictures of the crater spurting out sulfur smoke and then descend to the volcano base via other side of the volcano and take a dip in one of the hot spring pools to refresh yourself then return back to hotel for breakfast and then drive back to Medan, arrival at Medan check in to hotel.<br><b><br>DAY 07: HOTEL â€“ AIRPORTÂ  (B)<br></b>After breakfast transfer to Kualanamu Airport for your flight to next destination.<br></p><p><b>Included :</b><br>- Accommodation based on twin sharing <br>- Air condition private car <br>- Daily breakfast <br>- Tours <br>- Transfers <br>- Entrance fee <br>- English speaking tour guide <br>- jungle tracking (02 days / 01 nights) included local guide, permit, camping equipment and meals<br>- Full day white water rafting at Wampu river <br>- Sibayak Volcano climbing included local guide & permit.<br><br><b>Excluded : </b><br>- Airfare, Airport tax, Insurance, donation, tips, camera permit and all personal gratuities.<br><br><br></p>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        '),
(28, '07 DAYS MEDAN â€“ BRASTAGI â€“ KETAMBE AND LAKE TOBA TOUR', 'Incredible trip to see wild Sumatra Orang Utan at Ketambe and The Biggest Volcanic Lake In South East Asia. Great Experiences, adventure, nature, culture and leisure. Discover the highlight of Sumatra tour.<br>					                                					                                					                                ', '', '<p align=\"justify\"><b>                                                    DAY 01: AIRPORT / MEDAN â€“ HOTEL (Emerald Garden Hotel /Le Polonia Hotel / similar) <br></b>Arrival at Kualanamu International Airport pick up by our driver and then drive to hotel in Medan city, afternoon free at own leisure.</p><p align=\"justify\"><b>DAY 02: MEDAN â€“ BRASTAGI (Sinabung Hills Hotel / Sibayak Intl Hotel / Grand Mutiara Hotel)Â Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast city tour in Medan visiting Sultan Palace, Grand Mosque, Chinese temple, Hinduâ€™s temple and Kesawan Area â€the old center of Medan cityâ€ then drive to Brastagi, a cool and pleasant mountain area, on the way passing Sembahe and Sibolangit, arrival at Brastagi visiting Lhumbini Park with its duplicate of Shwedagon temple and then visiting fruit market and Gundaling Hill to see fantastic view to Sibayak and Sinabung Volcano (weather depends), afternoon check-in to hotel.<br><br><b>DAY 03: BRASTAGI â€“ KETAMBE (Thousand Hill Guesthouse / Friendship Guesthouse)Â Â Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast drive to Ketambe, on the way visit Batak Karo traditional village at Lingga and then continue drive by passing Bukit Barisan with stop at several interesting places, arriving in Ketambe check-in at simple guesthouse.<br>Â <br><b>DAY 04: FULLDAY JUNGLE TRACKINGÂ Â Â Â Â  (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast tracking at Ketambe (Leuser National Park), to explore the primary tropical rain-forest with its wildlife living in their natural habitat. You will go deeper into the jungle where you will have chances to see the wild Orangutans, Gibbons, Monkeys, Deer, Wild Pigs and kind of birds. You will also see special plants and insects of the Sumatra jungle. You may enjoy hot, warm and cold bath as the hot water is flowing into the river and mix up with the cold. Afternoon return to guesthouse.<br>Â <br><b>DAY 05: KETAMBE â€“ SAMOSIR ISLANDÂ Â  (B) <br></b>Early in the morning at 7.00 you proceed the journey to Samosir island via Sidikalang and Tele and at Tele stop to enjoy fantastic view of Lake Toba, afternoon arriving on Samosir Island check-in to hotel.<br></p><p align=\"justify\"><b>DAY 06: SAMOSIR EXCURSIONÂ Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast excursion on Samosir Island by car, visiting several Batak Toba traditional villages at :<br>- Ambarita : to see stone chairs and tables the old meeting place of Sialagan Kings.<br>- Simanindo : to see Batak Toba traditional dances and museum.<br>- Tomok : to see the old tombs of Sidabutar Kings<br>along on this trip also possible to stop at school to see the activities of young children in the school, visiting the village where the people make traditional hand weaving + stop also at scenic places like the graves! Afternoon return back to hotel<br>Â <br><b>DAY 07: SAMOSIR â€“ MEDAN / AIRPORTÂ Â Â Â  (B)<br></b>After breakfast crossing back to Parapat and then drive to Medan via Pematang Siantar and Tebing Tinggi, stop will be made at several interesting places, this trip will take about 5 hours driving . Arrival in Medan directly transferred to airport for your flight to next destination. TOUR ENDS<br>Â <br><b>Price included:<br></b>- Accommodation based on twin sharing <br>- Daily breakfast at hotel<br>- Air condition private car included driver, fuel, parking fee and driver accommodation<br>- Tours<br>- Transfers<br>- Entrance fees<br>- Full day Jungle tracking at Ketambe included: local guide and permit<br>- English speaking tour guide.<br>Â <br><b>Price Excluded:<br></b>- Airfare, airport tax, insurance, donations, tips, lunch, dinner, camera permit at national park and all personal gratuities.</p>                                                                                                                                                            '),
